For the month of September i have come back to buying games here are the games that I have bought September 2019 first 
The legend of Zelda wind waker HD i bought this online very cheap my favorite looking legend of Zelda games I am a fan toon link 
Second game this was a game I never gotten for the 3DS when it first release Star Fox 3DS this was a Walmart clearance fine for 10 bucks very cheap also 
Third Spyro reignited trilogy this was a must have for me because I am fan of Spyro after playing it it looked okay 
Fourth another legend of Zelda game which is new legend of Zelda links awakening this is a remastered from game boy game from 1993 which I still haven’t played it yet and a amiibo too 
Fifth which is a crossover game Mario and rabbis kingdom battle fun game cool crossover 
Sixth this game was available in japan only Kamen rider climax scramble I am a massive rider fan and this game is a another must for me I am not sure it will work for U.S switches and finally 
Seventh an old but new jrpg dragon quest 11 definitive edition the switch version only thing I know is coupled this that are fixed from the ps4 version and I’m glad I bought this to get into the dragon quest series because hero from the dragon quest is in smash ultimate and wanted to try it out that all seven games of September 2019 #nintendo #nintendoswitch #videogames #legendofzelda #windwakerhd #linksawakeningremake #amiibo #spyroreignitedtrilogy #starfox643d

caption.text:
Super Mario Kart
1992
.
Would you believe I just added this to my collection today. Well, I did have this game as a kid and believe me it got played a ton! Many, many nights were spent staying up super late with friends having some of the best times.
.
Although it’s an absolute classic, launched one of the best racing game series to this day, but this one definitely feels like 1992. Another reason why it took me so long to pick this up, is folks want a fortune for it, luckily I got it cheap and it has a great home up on the SNES shelf for many years to come.
.

“I just pray that this fighting will end as swiftly as possible. No one desires this war.”
Spoilers for the Sacred Stones ahead
Drawing 263. Eirika is the princess of the kingdom of Renais and twin sister of Crown Prince Ephraim in the GBA Fire Emblem: Sacred Stones. Her father makes her leave after the kingdom of Grado attacks her homeland. Her father’s trusted Knight Seth travels with her and gives her a rapier. They head to the kingdom of Frelia and her her friend and princess of Frelia, Tana, who is being held hostage by Grado troops. With the help of some soldiers, they rescue Tana. After this, they head to the Frelian castle to hear her father had been killed. Shocked, she vows to find her brother and keep him save and departs with a couple of soldiers from the kingdom. She finds out about her Lunar Brace she carries, as well as her brother’s, open a secret room where Renais’ stone is hidden. She learns from a cleric that Emperor Vigarde’s plan to destroy the Sacred Stones that safeguard the land from evil. She meets up with Ephraim and together with their band of soldiers and warriors discover that Lyon, their child hood friend and son of the Emperor who started the war was behind it all. They eventually destroy the real culprit of the war, a demon named Firmotiis.
Eirika is a kind hearted and forgiving perosn. Dex Entry:Electrouble the Ball Pokemon Evolved form of Montagna Electrode. Electrouble evolved from the presence of Voltorb and other Montagna Electrode and only exist in the Montagna Region. Electrouble look like different kinds of existing pokeballs but so far all Electrouble only look like 5 existing pokeballs even the rare Masterball. Electrouble often attack together and are very hard to deal with often attacking using high bolts of electricity. They can still shrink and use this to their advantage to escape from more dangerous Pokémon. Electrouble are very rarely seen separated, usually only separating whenever they fight each other however they can come back together after a while. Despite being tightly packed with each other they are surprisingly fast.
Type:Electric/Steel

Golf Magazine Presents 36 Great Holes Starring Fred Couples is a golf video game for the Sega 32X. The game features Fred Couples on the cover and is sponsored by Golf Magazine. It was released in 1994 in the North America, Japan, and Europe regions.

The game uses 12 male and 12 female players, and is set at 27 golfcourses around the USA. (Source @wikipedia)

Brutal Mario (鬼畜王マリオ Kichiku Ou Mario, Brutal King Mario), also known as Super Kitiku Mario, is a Super Mario World ROM hack created by a mysterious Japanese ROM-hacker who goes by the name of Carol.

It's well known for being a hack with a large amount of custom bosses and ASM gimmicks, with its development being started when such things were but a dream in the SMW hacking scene.

The hack contains several references to many other video games, from Final Fantasy, to Twinbee, to Kirby, to Mega Man, to even Cho Aniki of all things. (Source brutalmario.fandom.com)

Grand Theft Auto: Vice City Official Soundtrack Box Set is a seven-disc compilation CD box set containing music from the video game Grand Theft Auto: Vice City, each disc representing one of the game's seven music radio stations. It was released internationally on October 29, 2002. As well as the complete box set, the seven CDs were also released for purchase individually.

European editions of several of the CDs contain extra songs that are not found on US pressings (some of these songs do not actually appear in the game itself). Although the majority of the music from the game is included on the soundtracks, most of the CDs do not feature every song heard on the relevant radio station — in the US, only the Emotion 98.3 CD is complete, while in Europe the Emotion 98.3 and Fever 105 soundtracks are complete.

In addition to music, each CD also includes several specially-recorded DJ tracks containing dialogue from the station's host and station idents, plus two radio commercials heard in the game. With the exception of the Wildstyle disc, the final commercial track on each CD additionally contains an unlisted DJ talk segment hidden after a lengthy pause, containing further humorous dialogue from the station host (which typically results in their being fired or storming out of the recording studio). The two talk radio stations heard in Grand Theft Auto: Vice City (KCHAT, VCPR) did not receive a CD release and as such have never been released outside of the game. A Greatest Hits compilation CD was also released in North America the following year, containing a selection of songs from the full set plus the "Theme from Vice City". (Source gta.fandom.com)

Mortal Kombat (MK) is an arcade fighting game developed and published by Midway in 1992 as the first title in the Mortal Kombat series. It was subsequently released by Acclaim Entertainment for nearly every home platform of the time. The game focuses on several characters of various intentions who enter a martial arts tournament with worldly consequences. It introduced many key aspects of the Mortal Kombat series, including the unique five-button control scheme and gory finishing moves called Fatalities. (Source @wikipedia)

preview_comments.text: That is a good play!! 😉 That is similar to when I do a little damage to my opponent (but should be enough to mess up their recovery) while I play as R.O.B.. I use his Gyro move as the opponent tries to recover, then if timed right, the gyro will hit the recovering CPU and they won't rise high enough to grab a ledge, thus falling helplessly to the blast zone. This type of techinque is called "gimping," doing an attack that does a small amount of damage, but should be enough to mess up your opponents, mostly when they try to get back to the stage.

Pokemon Center Mega Tokyo!! I absolutely love this store, there’s so many different Pokemon items to choose from. Charms, TCG, figures, shirts, and my favorite thing plushies!
